commit.message:
Dummy commit

I think this might be needed to get Travis to run...?
Update Trove classifiers to use specific versions

Completely remove references to homebrew

Since we're not installing anything anymore this should be fine.

Try removing brew install swig

Since the swig output is in version control now, we don't actually need
swig in the build env.

The OSX build is failing during swig install because glib is required
and glib requires Python 3.8 and that can't be linked successfully.

Change README to only mention 3.6+ (and 2.7)

Nothing about actually supported versions has changed, but just bumping
this up for now. In particular since there has been no followup on the
OSX 3.5 issue, it seems fine to remove mention of 3.5 for now since it's
only a few more months until end-of-life for it.
Add note to error message about not having to use English
Remove section on building with ipadic
Add note that issues don't have to be in English
Remove extra newline in cli wrapper output

Add command line scripts

This includes one script that works as a command-line MeCab replacement
and one that spits out dictionary info.

Remove chasen format example from README

Chasen format is specified in the config that comes with IPAdic, but not
in Unidic, so if you use Unidic that fails. Replace it with a normal
tagger.

Add tip about trying args with Model

See #45 for details. For some reason the Tagger constructor doesn't
produce error strings, but the Model constructor does. Since the arg
format is the same you can get an error by passing it to the Model.

May want to automate that if it turns out this is an upstream bug that
can't be fixed.
